                     Leaving the CBD behind and flying westward, we follow the magnificent Magaliesberg mountain range; these quartzite cliffs head towards Hartbeespoort Dam. According to Geologists, these are among the oldest mountains in the world, almost 100 times older than Everest. Your view from the sky is truly the best way to appreciate the exquisite scenery below. While flying around the town and dam wall, you will understand why Hartbeespoort is one of the most popular tourist and hiking destinations in Gauteng, South Africa. <br />
                     <br /> Routing south-east back to Midrand, you will have the option to overfly either Lanseria Airport or Atteridgeville Township. Landing for lunch is an option on this leg of the flight, depending on the aforementioned decision. 
                     <br /> Alternatively, the route can be flown in reverse and departure from Lanseria Airport can be arranged. 
                     <br><br>This flight would be approximately 1 hour excluding time on the ground for your meal. Additionally, we can add to your tour, champagne, canap&eacute;s or flowers. Please ask us for a quote as prices are frequently subject to change.
